    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-gochujang-xl-lean-pork-bibimbap-with-spinach-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>mince</strong> (remove the paper if required!) with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for 8-10 min or until cooked through (no pink meat!), browned and crispy, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p><p>(Doubled your protein? Use 2 pans!)</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-gochujang-xl-lean-pork-bibimbap-with-spinach-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>cucumber</strong> in half lengthways, then slice finely</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-gochujang-xl-lean-pork-bibimbap-with-spinach-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>gochujang paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>tomato ketchup </strong>in a bowl with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>gochujang ketchup</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-gochujang-xl-lean-pork-bibimbap-with-spinach-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pork is cooked, add <strong>half </strong>the <strong>gochujang ketchup</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) to the pan and stir it all together until the pork in fully coated \u2013 this is your <strong>gochujang mince</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-gochujang-xl-lean-pork-bibimbap-with-spinach-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pork is coated, push the <strong>gochujang mince</strong> to one side of the pan and crack your <strong>egg[s] </strong>onto the other side</p><p>Cover with a lid and cook for 2-3 min or until done to your liking</p><p>Tip: Give your egg a little shake before you crack for a perfectly centred yolk!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-gochujang-xl-lean-pork-bibimbap-with-spinach-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add your <strong>toasted sesame oil </strong>and <strong>spinach </strong>to the pot with the <strong>cooked rice</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up until the spinach starts to wilt \u2013 this is your <strong>spinach rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/korean-style-gochujang-xl-lean-pork-bibimbap-with-spinach-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>gochujang lean pork</strong> with the <strong>spinach rice</strong> and <strong>sliced cucumber</strong> to the side and top with the <strong>fried egg</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>Korean-style gochujang XL lean pork bibimbap</strong></p><p>Drizzle over the <strong>remaining gochujang ketchup </strong>and garnish with your <strong>toasted sesame seeds</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
